&lt;li>include/posix/unistd.h&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#d0d0d0;background-color:#202020;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#cd2828;font-weight:bold">#ifdef __USE_MISC
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#cd2828;font-weight:bold">&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic">/* Invoke `system call&amp;#39; number SYSNO, passing it the remaining arguments.
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic"> This is completely system-dependent, and not often useful.
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic"> In Unix, `syscall&amp;#39; sets `errno&amp;#39; for all errors and most calls return -1
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic"> for errors; in many systems you cannot pass arguments or get return
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic"> values for all system calls (`pipe&amp;#39;, `fork&amp;#39;, and `getppid&amp;#39; typically
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic"> among them).
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic"> In Mach, all system calls take normal arguments and always return an
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#999;font-style:italic"> error code (zero for success). */&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#6ab825;font-weight:bold">extern&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#6ab825;font-weight:bold">long&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#6ab825;font-weight:bold">int&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#447fcf">syscall&lt;/span> (&lt;span style="color:#6ab825;font-weight:bold">long&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#6ab825;font-weight:bold">int&lt;/span> __sysno, ...) __THROW;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
